```

Then, running `./contour_test` will execute the tests.

### Conclusion

This example demonstrates creating a test fixture with Google Test to setup test preconditions (`SetUp()`) and then define multiple tests using this fixture. It provides a simple, reusable setup for multiple tests, ensuring each test starts with the same initial state defined in `SetUp()`. Notably, using fixtures is highly beneficial for larger and more complex test scenarios.
